The paper deals with the problem of detecting malware-infected computers and malicious web domains based on their encrypted HTTPS traffic. This problem falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper proposes a transfer learning approach based on sluice networks, which involves training models jointly to bootstrap each other. This approach involves machine learning techniques, which fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves the analysis of network traffic data, which falls under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). Finally, the paper proposes a new detection model, which involves software engineering techniques, falling under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
